From: ROCKNIX
Subject: [PATCH] board: rockchip: use root DTB filenames for RGxx3

ROCKNIX stores RK3566 device trees under /device_trees without the
rockchip/ prefix. Minime stores the same DTB filenames under
.system/devices. Keep U-Boot's detected fdtfile compatible with those
boot partition paths.

Imported from ROCKNIX RK3566 Generic U-Boot support and adapted for
U-Boot 2026.04 context.

Signed-off-by: ROCKNIX <noreply@rocknix.org>
---
 board/anbernic/rgxx3_rk3566/rgxx3-rk3566.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/board/anbernic/rgxx3_rk3566/rgxx3-rk3566.c
+++ b/board/anbernic/rgxx3_rk3566/rgxx3-rk3566.c
@@ -39,7 +39,7 @@
 
 #define GPIO_WRITEMASK(bits)	((bits) << 16)
 
-#define DTB_DIR			"rockchip/"
+#define DTB_DIR			""
 
 struct rg3xx_model {
 	const u16 adc_value;
